    {
      "content": "How to install and configure Azure PowerShell",
      "pos": [
        449,
        494
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "PowerShell<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;/a&gt;&lt;a href=\"/manage/install-and-configure-cli/\" title=\"Azure CLI\"&gt;</ph>Azure  CLI",
      "pos": [
        645,
        732
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use Windows PowerShell to perform a variety of tasks in Azure, either interactively at a command prompt or automatically through scripts.",
      "pos": [
        744,
        889
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure PowerShell is a module that provides cmdlets to manage Azure through Windows PowerShell.",
      "pos": [
        890,
        984
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use the cmdlets to create, test, deploy, and manage solutions and services delivered through the Azure platform.",
      "pos": [
        985,
        1105
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In most cases, you can use the cmdlets to perform the same tasks that you can perform through the Azure Management Portal.",
      "pos": [
        1106,
        1228
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For example, you can create and configure cloud services, virtual machines, virtual networks, and web apps.",
      "pos": [
        1229,
        1336
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The module is distributed as a downloadable file and the source code is managed through a publicly available repository.",
      "pos": [
        1338,
        1458
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "A link to the downloadable files is provided in the installation instructions later in this topic.",
      "pos": [
        1459,
        1557
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "For information about the source code, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Azure PowerShell code repository<ept id=\"p1\">](https://github.com/Azure/azure-powershell)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        1558,
        1679
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This guide provides basic information about installing and setting up Azure PowerShell to manage the Azure platform.",
      "pos": [
        1681,
        1797
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        1803,
        1862
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">&lt;a id=\"Prereq\"&gt;</ph><ph id=\"ph2\">&lt;/a&gt;</ph>Prerequisites for using Azure PowerShell"
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure is a subscription-based platform.",
      "pos": [
        1864,
        1903
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This means that a subscription is required to use the platform.",
      "pos": [
        1904,
        1967
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "In most cases, it also means that the cmdlets require subscription information to perform the tasks with your subscription.",
      "pos": [
        1968,
        2091
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "(Some of the storage-related cmdlets can be used without this information.) You provide this by configuring your computer to connect to your subscription.",
      "pos": [
        2092,
        2246
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Instructions are provided in this article, under \"How to: Connect to your subscription.\"",
      "pos": [
        2247,
        2335
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        2339,
        2446
      ],
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> Beginning in version 0.8.5, the Azure PowerShell modules require Microsoft .NET Framework 4.5."
    },
    {
      "content": "When you install the module, the installer checks your system for the required software and installs all dependencies, such as the correct version of Windows PowerShell and .NET Framework.",
      "pos": [
        2448,
        2636
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "How to: Install Azure PowerShell",
      "pos": [
        2662,
        2694
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can download and install the Azure PowerShell modules by running the <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Microsoft Web Platform Installer<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=320376)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2696,
        2853
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When prompted, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>Run<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        2854,
        2883
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The Web Platform Installer installs the Azure PowerShell modules and all dependencies.",
      "pos": [
        2884,
        2970
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Follow the prompts to complete the installation.",
      "pos": [
        2971,
        3019
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "<ph id=\"ph1\">[AZURE.NOTE]</ph> If you just want to download the PowerShell installer, please visit https://github.com/Azure/azure-powershell/releases.",
      "pos": [
        3023,
        3155
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Source code for the PowerShell cmdlets can be found at this repo as well",
      "pos": [
        3156,
        3228
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        3230,
        3374
      ],
      "content": "For more information about the command-line tools available for Azure, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Command-line tools<ept id=\"p1\">]( http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=320796)</ept>."
    },
    {
      "content": "Installing the module also installs a customized console for Azure PowerShell.",
      "pos": [
        3376,
        3454
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can run the cmdlets from either the standard Windows PowerShell console or the Azure PowerShell console.",
      "pos": [
        3455,
        3563
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The method you use to open either console depends on the version of Windows you're running:",
      "pos": [
        3565,
        3656
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "On a computer running at least Windows 8 or Windows Server 2012, you can use the built-in Search.",
      "pos": [
        3660,
        3757
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "From the Start screen, begin typing <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>power<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        3758,
        3804
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "This returns a scoped list of apps that includes Windows PowerShell and Azure PowerShell.",
      "pos": [
        3805,
        3894
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To open the console, click either app.",
      "pos": [
        3895,
        3933
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "(To pin the app to the Start screen, right-click the icon.)",
      "pos": [
        3934,
        3993
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "On a computer running a version earlier than Windows 8 or Windows Server 2012, use the Start menu.",
      "pos": [
        3997,
        4095
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "From the Start menu, click <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>All Programs<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>, click <bpt id=\"p2\">**</bpt>Azure<ept id=\"p2\">**</ept>, and then click <bpt id=\"p3\">**</bpt>Azure PowerShell<ept id=\"p3\">**</ept>.",
