      "content": "If you don't have a subscription, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Get Started with Azure<ept id=\"p1\">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/p/?LinkId=320795)</ept>.",
      "pos": [
        4296,
        4408
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "The cmdlets need your subscription so they can manage your services.",
      "pos": [
        4410,
        4478
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "There are two ways to provide your subscription information to Windows PowerShell.",
      "pos": [
        4479,
        4561
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "You can use a management certificate that contains the information or you can sign in to Azure using your Microsoft account or a work or school account.",
      "pos": [
        4562,
        4714
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you sign in, Azure Active Directory (Azure AD) authenticates the credentials and returns an access token that lets Azure PowerShell manage your account.",
      "pos": [
        4715,
        4872
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "To help you choose the authentication method that's appropriate for your needs, consider the following:",
      "pos": [
        4874,
        4977
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Azure AD is the recommended authentication method since it makes it easier to manage access to a subscription.",
      "pos": [
        4981,
        5091
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "With the update in version 0.8.6, it enables an automation scenario with Azure AD authentication as well if a work or school account is used.",
      "pos": [
        5092,
        5233
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "It works with Azure Resource Manager API as well.",
      "pos": [
        5234,
        5283
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "When you use the certificate method, the subscription information is available as long as the subscription and the certificate are valid.",
      "pos": [
        5286,
        5423
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "However, this method makes it harder to manage access to a shared subscription, such as when more than one person is authorized to access the account.",
      "pos": [
        5424,
        5574
      ]
    },
    {
      "content": "Also, Azure Resource Manager API doesn't accept certificate authentication.",
      "pos": [
        5575,
        5650
      ]
    },
    {
      "pos": [
        5652,
        5842
      ],
